      • extractCounterFromText

        public int extractCounterFromText(java.lang.String sText,
                         java.lang.String sStartSearchAfter,
                         java.lang.String sEndSearchBefore)
        Utility to extract numerical counter embedded in document type filter option text The counter is the string contained between two substrings provided e.g. "(1 - 15 of 62)", point start to string index 5 (iStartBracket) & end to index 7 (iEndBracket)
        Parameters:
        sText - contains the complete text from a specific specific filter option
        sStartSearchAfter - contains substring where to start extraction
        sEndSearchBefore - contains substring where to end extraction
        Returns:
        iCounter contains the numerical value of the counter extracted
